caller_intent: Delphina Lewis wanted to clarify an email she received about her policy renewal, confirm if there was any action needed, and verify the status of her upcoming renewals.
resolution_steps: Cody acknowledged the email confusion and checked the agency's records.
Cody confirmed the policy renewal dates (homeowner's on January 13th, auto on February 5th).
Cody explained the email was a reminder from the agency, not a direct communication from Cody.
Cody advised Delphina to wait for the policy packet and offered future assistance if needed.
knowledge_required: Understanding of agency email practices (reminder emails for renewals)
Policy renewal timelines and triggers for communication
Ability to check internal systems for policy details
systems_referenced: Carrier portals (implied through renewal date references)
summary: Delphina Lewis called to clarify an email about her policy renewal. Cody explained the email was a standard agency reminder, confirmed her renewal dates, and advised her to wait for the policy packet. The conversation resolved her confusion and ended with mutual understanding.
